# Healthera.AI Platform

A DeFi healthcare lending platform built with Next.js, React, and Tailwind CSS.

## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have installed:
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (v16.8 or higher)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/) (usually comes with Node.js)
- [Git](https://git-scm.com/)
- [Visual Studio Code](https://code.visualstudio.com/) (recommended)

### Installation

1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/Rebeccca2000/healthera_ai.git
cd healthera-platform
```

2. Install dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

3. Set up required components
```bash
# Initialize shadcn/ui
npx shadcn-ui@latest init

# Add required components
npx shadcn-ui@latest add card
```

### Running the Development Server

1. Start the development server:
```bash
npm run dev
```

2. Open your browser and navigate to:
```
http://localhost:3000
```

## 📁 Project Structure

```
src/
├── app/                 # Next.js app directory
│   ├── page.tsx        # Home page
│   └── layout.tsx      # Root layout
├── components/         # React components
│   ├── ui/            # UI components
│   │   └── card.tsx   # Card component
│   └── Dashboard.tsx  # Main dashboard component
├── lib/               # Utility functions
│   └── utils.ts      # Helper utilities
└── styles/           # CSS styles
    └── globals.css   # Global styles
```

## 🛠️ Development

### Technology Stack

- **Framework**: Next.js 13+ with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui
- **Icons**: Lucide React

### Key Features

- Modern, dark-themed dashboard interface
- User profile management
- Loan request handling
- Real-time metrics display
- Responsive design

### Common Issues & Solutions

1. **Module Not Found Errors**
```bash
# Clear dependencies and reinstall
rm -rf node_modules
npm cache clean --force
npm install
```

2. **TypeScript Errors**
- Ensure `tsconfig.json` is properly configured
- Run `npm run build` to check for type errors

3. **Style Issues**
- Check if Tailwind CSS is properly initialized
- Verify `globals.css` includes required directives

